A RESOLUTION
To commend Margaret "Mimi" Stoker on the occasion of her induction into the Louisiana
4-H Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, Margaret "Mimi" Stoker holds bachelor's and master's degrees from
Northwestern State University, and she completed post-graduate studies with an emphasis
on environmental science at Louisiana State University; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Stoker worked for the LSU AgCenter for thirty-two years in a
variety of roles, including as a 4-H agent in Rapides and Tangipahoa Parishes, a home
economist in Sabine and Natchitoches Parishes, and an environmental agent for Northwest
Louisiana; she developed, presented, and administered the Environmental Educational
Program for a thirteen-parish region and served as president of the LSU Extension Agents
Professional Association; and
WHEREAS, Mimi Stoker served the Department of Environmental Quality as a
watershed coordinator during the Cane River Watershed Grant Project and served four years
as an elected member of the Natchitoches Parish Police Jury; she also worked as a
hospitality management instructor at the Sabine Valley campus of Central Louisiana
Technical Community College; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Stoker is a former office manager and current parenting instructor
at the Women's Resource Center; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Stoker has been a member of the Natchitoches Lions Club since
2007; she serves the club as an executive board member of the Louisiana Lions Children's
Camp and Lions Eye Foundation, and she is a Melvin Jones Fellow; and
